WEBVTT

00:00:10.200 --> 00:00:33.159 align:middle line:90%
[Music_]

00:00:33.159 --> 00:00:34.992 align:middle line:84%
>>Regina Meredith: We've
all seen the movies

00:00:34.992 --> 00:00:37.322 align:middle line:84%
and read the books where
the American or English girl

00:00:37.322 --> 00:00:40.297 align:middle line:84%
goes to Italy or Spain and falls
for the love of their lives.

00:00:40.297 --> 00:00:43.033 align:middle line:84%
It's such a common theme
that it's become a cliche,

00:00:43.033 --> 00:00:45.569 align:middle line:84%
but cliches generally
have an underlying truth.

00:00:45.569 --> 00:00:48.109 align:middle line:84%
So what is it that has
become out of balance

00:00:48.109 --> 00:00:50.674 align:middle line:84%
in our society that sends us
looking for something other

00:00:50.674 --> 00:00:53.243 align:middle line:84%
than in terms of
romantic partners?

00:00:53.243 --> 00:00:56.180 align:middle line:84%
Andre Villa would say it's
because we've lost our template

00:00:56.180 --> 00:00:57.735 align:middle line:90%
for becoming men and women.

00:00:57.735 --> 00:01:00.199 align:middle line:84%
Andrea works with youth
in helping them find

00:01:00.199 --> 00:01:01.418 align:middle line:90%
their strength and courage.

00:01:01.418 --> 00:01:03.087 align:middle line:84%
And thank you for
joining us today.

00:01:03.087 --> 00:01:05.754 align:middle line:84%
This is an interesting
conversation and one that's

00:01:05.754 --> 00:01:07.091 align:middle line:90%
uncomfortable for some people.

00:01:07.091 --> 00:01:11.028 align:middle line:84%
We tried so hard to get this
politically correct androgenous

00:01:11.028 --> 00:01:12.882 align:middle line:84%
thing going that
we've succeeded.

00:01:12.882 --> 00:01:15.299 align:middle line:84%
And there are a lot of problems
that are coming out of it.

00:01:15.299 --> 00:01:17.835 align:middle line:84%
So before we even
get into all of that,

00:01:17.835 --> 00:01:20.771 align:middle line:84%
let's talk about your own
youth, because you were raised

00:01:20.771 --> 00:01:23.207 align:middle line:84%
in Italy, you had maybe
a different template

00:01:23.207 --> 00:01:26.047 align:middle line:84%
than an American
had in the way you

00:01:26.047 --> 00:01:29.613 align:middle line:84%
were raised and coming into
your manhood as a young fellow.

00:01:29.613 --> 00:01:33.029 align:middle line:84%
And also questioning
the system that you were

00:01:33.029 --> 00:01:35.219 align:middle line:84%
plugged into, in
terms of education.

00:01:35.219 --> 00:01:37.287 align:middle line:90%
So tell us about yourself.

00:01:37.287 --> 00:01:40.586 align:middle line:84%
>> Andrea Villa: Well, I think
the most important thing that I

00:01:40.586 --> 00:01:44.428 align:middle line:84%
was blessed with, an
extended family --

00:01:44.428 --> 00:01:46.930 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina Meredith: Extended
families are huge, right.

00:01:46.930 --> 00:01:48.098 align:middle line:90%
>> Andrea Villa: Correct.

00:01:48.098 --> 00:01:53.904 align:middle line:84%
There was the grandfathers
present in my life,

00:01:53.904 --> 00:01:56.373 align:middle line:84%
especially when I
was a young kid.

00:01:56.373 --> 00:02:00.110 align:middle line:84%
And they were sort of the
custodian of the family lore

00:02:00.110 --> 00:02:05.315 align:middle line:84%
and the custodian of the
heroic struggle of my family,

00:02:05.315 --> 00:02:08.952 align:middle line:84%
with invasions, Germans
every twenty years or so,

00:02:08.952 --> 00:02:12.189 align:middle line:84%
seems they like to vacation
with their arms in Italy.

00:02:12.189 --> 00:02:16.960 align:middle line:84%
So a lot of disruption and
acts of heroism and so forth.

00:02:16.960 --> 00:02:20.364 align:middle line:84%
So I really grew up with a
real sense of where I was from.

00:02:20.364 --> 00:02:24.802 align:middle line:84%
All this story telling
around the kitchen

00:02:24.802 --> 00:02:30.341 align:middle line:84%
table, all these questions,
boys are very, very curious.

00:02:30.341 --> 00:02:33.310 align:middle line:84%
So this one element,
the other element

00:02:33.310 --> 00:02:37.114 align:middle line:84%
that was I was really
blessed, I think, was nature.

00:02:37.114 --> 00:02:42.653 align:middle line:84%
I really, you know, I was --
we wanted to spend time out.

00:02:42.653 --> 00:02:47.396 align:middle line:84%
So that allowed me to
have spent hours in,

00:02:47.396 --> 00:02:51.394 align:middle line:84%
you know, in the river,
on the river canyon,

00:02:51.394 --> 00:02:53.497 align:middle line:90%
and territory belonged to kids.

00:02:53.497 --> 00:02:57.368 align:middle line:84%
And so there was
this element, we

00:02:57.368 --> 00:03:00.686 align:middle line:84%
were not supervised
so we have to sort

00:03:00.686 --> 00:03:02.673 align:middle line:90%
of like, deal with each other.

00:03:02.673 --> 00:03:06.410 align:middle line:84%
So there was no, like,
a little league play,

00:03:06.410 --> 00:03:09.869 align:middle line:84%
where the uniform, the games,
the referees and games,

00:03:09.869 --> 00:03:11.849 align:middle line:90%
intervention of the adults.

00:03:11.849 --> 00:03:13.299 align:middle line:84%
We had to settle
and negotiate out

00:03:13.299 --> 00:03:15.285 align:middle line:84%
of the scrapes we
were getting into,

00:03:15.285 --> 00:03:17.755 align:middle line:90%
and a boy will get into scrapes.

00:03:17.755 --> 00:03:21.724 align:middle line:84%
So it was this element, and
the third element that we had,

00:03:21.724 --> 00:03:23.227 align:middle line:90%
it was nature.

00:03:23.227 --> 00:03:27.698 align:middle line:84%
And nature really I
think when you belong,

00:03:27.698 --> 00:03:31.235 align:middle line:84%
where you really develop
a sense of belonging,

00:03:31.235 --> 00:03:35.739 align:middle line:84%
and it is basically where you
get your spiritual education.

00:03:35.739 --> 00:03:41.078 align:middle line:84%
So I think those three elements,
they were very, very strong

00:03:41.078 --> 00:03:43.334 align:middle line:84%
and that is one of
the first things

00:03:43.334 --> 00:03:46.233 align:middle line:84%
that you notice when you
come to this country,

00:03:46.233 --> 00:03:48.501 align:middle line:84%
especially when you
notice that, you know,

00:03:48.501 --> 00:03:51.421 align:middle line:84%
the parents, the grandfathers
are playing golf in Florida.

00:03:51.421 --> 00:03:56.827 align:middle line:84%
And that's really
something that is a problem

00:03:56.827 --> 00:03:58.394 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: It is a problem.

00:03:58.394 --> 00:04:02.452 align:middle line:84%
As you were saying earlier,
these heroic stories

00:04:02.452 --> 00:04:06.850 align:middle line:84%
are what you and your brothers
and your cousins and everyone

00:04:06.850 --> 00:04:09.304 align:middle line:84%
were raised on, and
yet the storyteller

00:04:09.304 --> 00:04:10.507 align:middle line:90%
was the grandfather.

00:04:10.507 --> 00:04:15.546 align:middle line:84%
Tell us a little bit about how
you perceived your grandfather

00:04:15.546 --> 00:04:17.905 align:middle line:84%
at that time, how
the grandfathers were

00:04:17.905 --> 00:04:19.583 align:middle line:90%
perceived within the family.

00:04:19.583 --> 00:04:21.919 align:middle line:84%
>> AV: You know, what's
what I learned from them,

00:04:21.919 --> 00:04:25.475 align:middle line:84%
they're all mentorship,
which is another figure

00:04:25.475 --> 00:04:28.358 align:middle line:84%
that's disappearing in the
culture of this course.

00:04:28.358 --> 00:04:32.129 align:middle line:84%
Mentors really is
what is -- as a role,

00:04:32.129 --> 00:04:35.197 align:middle line:84%
it's really interesting, not so
much for you to become a doctor

00:04:35.197 --> 00:04:37.935 align:middle line:84%
or an engineer but about
you becoming a good person.

00:04:37.935 --> 00:04:39.937 align:middle line:84%
You can only become
a good person

00:04:39.937 --> 00:04:42.739 align:middle line:84%
by becoming the you
that is living there.

00:04:42.739 --> 00:04:47.896 align:middle line:84%
So a lot of time spent
with my grandfathers

00:04:47.896 --> 00:04:50.447 align:middle line:84%
is questions, you know, what
do you think about this.

00:04:50.447 --> 00:04:53.795 align:middle line:84%
He was asking questions
of me more than I

00:04:53.795 --> 00:04:56.720 align:middle line:84%
a question of him,
especially one grandfather.

00:04:56.720 --> 00:04:59.430 align:middle line:84%
So it was really like -- it
was really drawing me out with

00:04:59.430 --> 00:05:01.597 align:middle line:84%
a process of inquiries, it
wasn't telling me this is

00:05:01.597 --> 00:05:03.927 align:middle line:84%
right, this is wrong,
like my father would do.

00:05:03.927 --> 00:05:05.963 align:middle line:84%
Because my father
is more concerning,

00:05:05.963 --> 00:05:08.959 align:middle line:90%
you know, getting it straight.

00:05:08.959 --> 00:05:11.001 align:middle line:84%
Grandfathers are more
concerned with who you are.

00:05:11.001 --> 00:05:13.225 align:middle line:84%
I think this was
the gift, and it's

00:05:13.225 --> 00:05:16.073 align:middle line:84%
kind of role modelling I try
to do when I work with my kids,

00:05:16.073 --> 00:05:19.798 align:middle line:84%
you know it's not about
me telling them, dumping

00:05:19.798 --> 00:05:24.281 align:middle line:84%
on them what I know, just
drawing what is there already.

00:05:24.281 --> 00:05:27.134 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: So what has
happened in our society,

00:05:27.134 --> 00:05:29.953 align:middle line:84%
in the west and in
America in particular,

00:05:29.953 --> 00:05:33.257 align:middle line:84%
there's become this huge
disconnect , almost a --

00:05:33.257 --> 00:05:36.727 align:middle line:84%
kind of a self serving quality
when people reach the years

00:05:36.727 --> 00:05:38.662 align:middle line:84%
where they become
grandparents, which is oh,

00:05:38.662 --> 00:05:39.930 align:middle line:90%
I'm done with all of that.

00:05:39.930 --> 00:05:43.200 align:middle line:84%
I'm out of here, and the
breaking up of family.

00:05:43.200 --> 00:05:46.704 align:middle line:84%
I too see this as something
that's had a devastating effect

00:05:46.704 --> 00:05:47.504 align:middle line:90%
on all of us.

00:05:47.504 --> 00:05:50.821 align:middle line:84%
I mean, what about -- what
about the person growing older

00:05:50.821 --> 00:05:52.676 align:middle line:84%
themselves, not so
have that connection?

00:05:52.676 --> 00:05:57.699 align:middle line:84%
>> AV: There's a sense of
rootedness that you get if you

00:05:57.699 --> 00:06:01.385 align:middle line:84%
connected with your
elders that is --

00:06:01.385 --> 00:06:06.023 align:middle line:84%
there's no money that can
pay for it, you know, it's --

00:06:06.023 --> 00:06:08.354 align:middle line:84%
it really provides a
sense of rootedness,

00:06:08.354 --> 00:06:10.227 align:middle line:84%
a sense of belonging
to something.

00:06:10.227 --> 00:06:12.496 align:middle line:84%
When I'm in my hometown
I know where I come from,

00:06:12.496 --> 00:06:15.065 align:middle line:84%
I know the rocks, I
know the territory,

00:06:15.065 --> 00:06:16.900 align:middle line:84%
I know what happened
there and then.

00:06:16.900 --> 00:06:19.004 align:middle line:84%
So there is a sense
walking the street

00:06:19.004 --> 00:06:21.939 align:middle line:84%
it's different from anybody
living in this country.

00:06:21.939 --> 00:06:25.638 align:middle line:84%
And when I work
with the boys I do

00:06:25.638 --> 00:06:30.412 align:middle line:84%
try to get to an experience
of rootedness in life >> RM:

00:06:30.412 --> 00:06:31.281 align:middle line:90%
Rootedness, right

00:06:31.281 --> 00:06:34.785 align:middle line:84%
>> AV: Because that gives the
energy and the power to deal

00:06:34.785 --> 00:06:36.453 align:middle line:90%
with the complexities.

00:06:36.453 --> 00:06:38.829 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: We were talking
off camera about this,

00:06:38.829 --> 00:06:41.081 align:middle line:84%
and I'll get into this
part of the conversation,

00:06:41.081 --> 00:06:45.236 align:middle line:84%
but the whole role of boys and
girls in Italy is defined very

00:06:45.236 --> 00:06:48.098 align:middle line:84%
differently than growing up in
the United States, for example.

00:06:48.098 --> 00:06:49.869 align:middle line:84%
And I'll just use
those two countries,

00:06:49.869 --> 00:06:52.703 align:middle line:84%
we're all various, you know,
iterations of it in between.

00:06:52.703 --> 00:06:55.524 align:middle line:84%
But the subject
of the girls being

00:06:55.524 --> 00:07:00.919 align:middle line:84%
able to be in themselves
kind of joyful and flirty,

00:07:00.919 --> 00:07:05.949 align:middle line:84%
and they can take up space with
their own being, so to speak.

00:07:05.949 --> 00:07:09.024 align:middle line:84%
More in Italy, you see this in
Italy where the girls in the US

00:07:09.024 --> 00:07:11.355 align:middle line:84%
are more like this,
with eyes cast down

00:07:11.355 --> 00:07:12.594 align:middle line:90%
and there's more fear.

00:07:12.594 --> 00:07:14.469 align:middle line:84%
And when we were talking
off camera about it,

00:07:14.469 --> 00:07:17.728 align:middle line:84%
you were saying because this
knowledge passed back and forth

00:07:17.728 --> 00:07:20.831 align:middle line:84%
between the grandfather, the
grandfather to the father

00:07:20.831 --> 00:07:24.134 align:middle line:84%
and to the son and out to the
cousins is you have to behave

00:07:24.134 --> 00:07:27.270 align:middle line:84%
in a certain way and
you don't essentially --

00:07:27.270 --> 00:07:30.774 align:middle line:84%
I say molest in the Spanish
sense of the word --

00:07:30.774 --> 00:07:33.411 align:middle line:84%
these girls, you don't bother
these girls in an inappropriate

00:07:33.411 --> 00:07:34.211 align:middle line:90%
way.

00:07:34.211 --> 00:07:37.014 align:middle line:84%
So they're free to just grow up
and be beautiful young women.

00:07:37.014 --> 00:07:39.590 align:middle line:84%
>> AV: This is one of the first
things you notice when you go

00:07:39.590 --> 00:07:43.687 align:middle line:84%
-- when I went back to
-- went back to Italy,

00:07:43.687 --> 00:07:48.625 align:middle line:84%
is when I visit there that the
women look at you, and here,

00:07:48.625 --> 00:07:50.427 align:middle line:84%
it never happens,
never look at you.

00:07:50.427 --> 00:07:52.903 align:middle line:84%
Because there's the sense
that if they look at you

00:07:52.903 --> 00:07:54.674 align:middle line:84%
they're inviting you
in a conversation,

00:07:54.674 --> 00:07:55.632 align:middle line:90%
they're inviting you --

00:07:55.632 --> 00:07:57.099 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: They feel unsafe.

00:07:57.099 --> 00:07:58.902 align:middle line:84%
>> AV: Correct,
they feel unsafe.

00:07:58.902 --> 00:08:03.982 align:middle line:84%
Whereas in Italy they look
at you with appreciation.

00:08:03.982 --> 00:08:07.608 align:middle line:84%
A handsome man is walking
by, that was interesting,

00:08:07.608 --> 00:08:09.479 align:middle line:90%
and I got a look at you.

00:08:09.479 --> 00:08:11.581 align:middle line:84%
I feel safe enough, and
it doesn't mean anything.

00:08:11.581 --> 00:08:14.017 align:middle line:84%
It means, like, oh,
I acknowledge you,

00:08:14.017 --> 00:08:15.185 align:middle line:90%
acknowledge as I pass by.

00:08:15.185 --> 00:08:20.086 align:middle line:84%
And this is very -- it's very
-- jumps to your eyes the moment

00:08:20.086 --> 00:08:23.693 align:middle line:84%
you get to Italy, this sense
of women are much more safe.

00:08:23.693 --> 00:08:25.462 align:middle line:90%
Also because they're protected.

00:08:25.462 --> 00:08:27.531 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: Talk about
that for a moment,

00:08:27.531 --> 00:08:33.537 align:middle line:84%
that's part of what the
men pass on to each other.

00:08:33.537 --> 00:08:34.938 align:middle line:90%
>> AV: Absolutely.

00:08:34.938 --> 00:08:39.976 align:middle line:84%
How shall we say this, you know,
I do this work with initiation,

00:08:39.976 --> 00:08:44.080 align:middle line:84%
and I think one of
the first initiation

00:08:44.080 --> 00:08:47.979 align:middle line:84%
is going to ask the lady out,
and they have to go and shake

00:08:47.979 --> 00:08:49.052 align:middle line:90%
the hands of the father.

00:08:49.052 --> 00:08:52.580 align:middle line:84%
The father knows exactly
well what you're up to,

00:08:52.580 --> 00:08:57.794 align:middle line:84%
so he's going to make sure
that you shake hands with him

00:08:57.794 --> 00:09:00.430 align:middle line:90%
and he's going to be present.

00:09:00.430 --> 00:09:03.088 align:middle line:84%
So if anything
wrong happens, see,

00:09:03.088 --> 00:09:08.198 align:middle line:84%
when I was growing up there
was a lot of hanky panky going

00:09:08.198 --> 00:09:12.459 align:middle line:84%
on -- but no trouble, because
I know there was any trouble I

00:09:12.459 --> 00:09:14.745 align:middle line:90%
would be a dead man.

00:09:14.745 --> 00:09:15.648 align:middle line:90%
Either the father --

00:09:15.648 --> 00:09:17.981 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: The brothers would
come after you or your father.

00:09:17.981 --> 00:09:20.517 align:middle line:84%
>> AV: So that create a lot
of safety for the women,

00:09:20.517 --> 00:09:25.747 align:middle line:84%
but also makes me be very
clear I'm committed to this

00:09:25.747 --> 00:09:27.791 align:middle line:90%
relationship or not.

00:09:27.791 --> 00:09:31.839 align:middle line:84%
So you know, courtship is
another rite of passage

00:09:31.839 --> 00:09:33.797 align:middle line:90%
that's gone, passed by.

00:09:33.797 --> 00:09:37.968 align:middle line:84%
You know, it's come very
easy for the boys and girls

00:09:37.968 --> 00:09:41.104 align:middle line:84%
to get together without
really the consequences

00:09:41.104 --> 00:09:42.439 align:middle line:90%
that in the old days.

00:09:42.439 --> 00:09:47.110 align:middle line:84%
Courting ritual is a very
important part of village life.

00:09:47.110 --> 00:09:52.015 align:middle line:84%
Got to make sure the guy is
Good enough and proving himself

00:09:52.015 --> 00:09:53.817 align:middle line:84%
so he can spend
time with the girl.

00:09:53.817 --> 00:10:01.858 align:middle line:84%
It's also something that in some
society involves very complex

00:10:01.858 --> 00:10:05.929 align:middle line:84%
ritual and going to
debt in order to --

00:10:05.929 --> 00:10:09.432 align:middle line:84%
for you to afford a
relationship with a woman,

00:10:09.432 --> 00:10:11.961 align:middle line:84%
and this debt is supported
by your community

00:10:11.961 --> 00:10:12.836 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Debt, you say?

00:10:12.836 --> 00:10:13.636 align:middle line:90%
>> AV: Yeah.

00:10:13.636 --> 00:10:14.471 align:middle line:90%
Debt, yeah.

00:10:14.471 --> 00:10:17.396 align:middle line:84%
So your community
makes sure, your family

00:10:17.396 --> 00:10:22.860 align:middle line:84%
makes sure you're supported in
doing this new adventure which

00:10:22.860 --> 00:10:24.548 align:middle line:90%
is the creation of new life.

00:10:24.548 --> 00:10:27.517 align:middle line:90%
So the old, very ritualized.

00:10:27.517 --> 00:10:30.520 align:middle line:84%
I won't say in Italy
was very ritualized,

00:10:30.520 --> 00:10:35.759 align:middle line:84%
but there was definitely an
awareness of who I'm dating

00:10:35.759 --> 00:10:39.262 align:middle line:84%
and what I'm dating is part
of a bigger conversation.

00:10:39.262 --> 00:10:41.765 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: And involves as
you say the community,

00:10:41.765 --> 00:10:45.435 align:middle line:84%
the entire family's support,
and agreement on some level.

00:10:45.435 --> 00:10:47.011 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I think
there are some people

00:10:47.011 --> 00:10:48.469 align:middle line:84%
listening who would
say, yeah, well

00:10:48.469 --> 00:10:50.384 align:middle line:84%
isn't that why people
who are in America

00:10:50.384 --> 00:10:52.521 align:middle line:84%
left Europe, for example,
so you didn't have

00:10:52.521 --> 00:10:54.144 align:middle line:90%
to be tied to these traditions.

00:10:54.144 --> 00:10:57.881 align:middle line:84%
Is there something that has been
a trade off or do you see this,

00:10:57.881 --> 00:11:00.102 align:middle line:84%
it's simply been a decline
in the social fabric?

00:11:00.102 --> 00:11:02.185 align:middle line:84%
>> AV: You know, when I
talk about it, this thing,

00:11:02.185 --> 00:11:05.355 align:middle line:84%
