was an extended conversation,

00:22:14.523 --> 00:22:19.495 align:middle line:84%
and he said if there were
a way to embrace the people

00:22:19.495 --> 00:22:23.633 align:middle line:84%
in our prison systems, give them
some pride in themselves back,

00:22:23.633 --> 00:22:27.336 align:middle line:84%
these people often have
very high levels of courage.

00:22:27.336 --> 00:22:30.473 align:middle line:84%
Whatever it took to break free
and express themselves even

00:22:30.473 --> 00:22:36.312 align:middle line:84%
in a criminal, harmful
way, very harmful at times,

00:22:36.312 --> 00:22:39.015 align:middle line:84%
but also a certain
element of creativity.

00:22:39.015 --> 00:22:43.152 align:middle line:84%
A lot of criminals -- they know
how to find their way through

00:22:43.152 --> 00:22:44.987 align:middle line:90%
the back alleys of life.

00:22:44.987 --> 00:22:49.592 align:middle line:84%
You're saying the unhealthy
result of squashing those

00:22:49.592 --> 00:22:52.712 align:middle line:84%
normal instincts for a boy
to just burst forward --

00:22:52.712 --> 00:22:55.037 align:middle line:84%
and girls, boys and
girls -- we're talking --

00:22:55.037 --> 00:22:58.134 align:middle line:84%
you mostly work with boys so
for now let's speak about them.

00:22:58.134 --> 00:23:03.272 align:middle line:84%
>> AV: There's a subtle
moment that doesn't happen.

00:23:03.272 --> 00:23:08.068 align:middle line:84%
In the old days, and then
we have all these problems

00:23:08.068 --> 00:23:10.026 align:middle line:84%
because, you know,
they have defiance,

00:23:10.026 --> 00:23:14.083 align:middle line:84%
they call it defiance disorder,
it makes me absolutely half.

00:23:14.083 --> 00:23:15.351 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Defiance disorder.

00:23:15.351 --> 00:23:17.019 align:middle line:84%
>> AV: When you
live with this --

00:23:17.019 --> 00:23:19.555 align:middle line:84%
when you live in terms of
defiance it's hell, right?

00:23:19.555 --> 00:23:22.460 align:middle line:84%
But you have to
understand that this

00:23:22.460 --> 00:23:25.761 align:middle line:84%
is the right place, the
right time, just as a father,

00:23:25.761 --> 00:23:28.898 align:middle line:90%
as a mother, you're exhausted.

00:23:28.898 --> 00:23:31.434 align:middle line:84%
You'll always be the
father and the mother,

00:23:31.434 --> 00:23:33.469 align:middle line:90%
but you've exhausted your roles.

00:23:33.469 --> 00:23:37.645 align:middle line:84%
The person now is ready
for the next step,

00:23:37.645 --> 00:23:41.260 align:middle line:84%
and the next step that
is covered, the next step

00:23:41.260 --> 00:23:44.947 align:middle line:84%
happens to ritual, it's
a ritual experience.

00:23:44.947 --> 00:23:48.851 align:middle line:84%
Not something that's logic, not
something that can be taught,

00:23:48.851 --> 00:23:52.355 align:middle line:84%
no teaching, it's an experience
the person has to undergo.

00:23:52.355 --> 00:23:56.525 align:middle line:84%
And then to reveal
something about themselves.

00:23:56.525 --> 00:24:00.568 align:middle line:84%
So it's that -- so up to now
it's been [INAUDIBLE] about

00:24:00.568 --> 00:24:02.932 align:middle line:90%
as bad as intellect, right?

00:24:02.932 --> 00:24:05.334 align:middle line:84%
We've been in track,
first grade, second grade.

00:24:05.334 --> 00:24:09.572 align:middle line:84%
Now we're going back to a
natural way of learning,

00:24:09.572 --> 00:24:13.542 align:middle line:84%
we're going to an experience,
an experience of a bigger self

00:24:13.542 --> 00:24:14.877 align:middle line:90%
than you get inside.

00:24:14.877 --> 00:24:19.648 align:middle line:84%
This is what -- and only this,
but it's a challenge also

00:24:19.648 --> 00:24:22.118 align:middle line:84%
to express this
gift in the world.

00:24:22.118 --> 00:24:25.688 align:middle line:84%
Because it's not enough to go as
nice as we can to the retreat,

00:24:25.688 --> 00:24:28.391 align:middle line:84%
have this beautiful
moment of life.

00:24:28.391 --> 00:24:30.288 align:middle line:84%
Then the most
important thing is I

00:24:30.288 --> 00:24:34.296 align:middle line:84%
want to see this gift
implemented in the world,

00:24:34.296 --> 00:24:36.232 align:middle line:84%
I want you to show
up in the world.

00:24:36.232 --> 00:24:39.886 align:middle line:84%
Because as you see one
of the biggest moments,

00:24:39.886 --> 00:24:43.505 align:middle line:84%
you know, to be
seen, to belong, is

00:24:43.505 --> 00:24:46.776 align:middle line:84%
one of the most
greatest human needs.

00:24:46.776 --> 00:24:50.297 align:middle line:84%
But they do come
at the forefront

00:24:50.297 --> 00:24:52.314 align:middle line:90%
when you're a teenager.

00:24:52.314 --> 00:24:58.020 align:middle line:84%
In fact, you know, they -- they
always belong to each other,

00:24:58.020 --> 00:25:00.372 align:middle line:84%
they always dress the same,
they're all individuals,

00:25:00.372 --> 00:25:01.690 align:middle line:90%
but they have --

00:25:01.690 --> 00:25:03.798 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: They have a great
need for acceptance among

00:25:03.798 --> 00:25:04.560 align:middle line:90%
themselves, yes.

00:25:04.560 --> 00:25:06.477 align:middle line:84%
>> AV: When I was 14 you
couldn't separate me.

00:25:06.477 --> 00:25:09.162 align:middle line:84%
I had this military
jacket, and I couldn't --

00:25:09.162 --> 00:25:10.941 align:middle line:90%
I was sleeping in it.

00:25:10.941 --> 00:25:13.108 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: My girlfriends and
I would call each other up

00:25:13.108 --> 00:25:15.171 align:middle line:84%
in the morning, what color
skirt are you wearing today,

00:25:15.171 --> 00:25:17.073 align:middle line:84%
are you going to wear your
little white skirts, yeah,

00:25:17.073 --> 00:25:18.441 align:middle line:90%
let's wear white today -- yeah.

00:25:18.441 --> 00:25:21.143 align:middle line:84%
>> AV: Because -- by
the way, this is like --

00:25:21.143 --> 00:25:24.132 align:middle line:84%
adolescence and teens,
it's a modern invention,

00:25:24.132 --> 00:25:25.414 align:middle line:90%
this didn't exist.

00:25:25.414 --> 00:25:27.852 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: What didn't exist?

00:25:27.852 --> 00:25:29.685 align:middle line:84%
>> AV: Up to 200 years
ago, it didn't exist.

00:25:29.685 --> 00:25:31.687 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: What didn't?

00:25:31.687 --> 00:25:32.655 align:middle line:90%
>> AV: Adolescence.

00:25:32.655 --> 00:25:33.956 align:middle line:90%
Either you're a boy --

00:25:33.956 --> 00:25:35.157 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Adolescence --

00:25:35.157 --> 00:25:36.559 align:middle line:84%
>> AV: Adolescence, yes,
I'm sorry, I apologize --

00:25:36.559 --> 00:25:38.994 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: I'll just say it for
you, if your accent -- yeah --

00:25:38.994 --> 00:25:43.865 align:middle line:84%
>> AV: So adolescence didn't
exist because we created this

00:25:43.865 --> 00:25:47.443 align:middle line:84%
holding tank which is called
school, then you know,

00:25:47.443 --> 00:25:50.753 align:middle line:84%
they spend all these years
that they usually spend with

00:25:50.753 --> 00:25:55.330 align:middle line:84%
their fathers learning a trade
or going for some adventures

00:25:55.330 --> 00:25:58.735 align:middle line:84%
somewhere in the world,
exploring -- anyway,

00:25:58.735 --> 00:26:02.866 align:middle line:84%
learning without a man, and it
was showing really the mettle

00:26:02.866 --> 00:26:06.000 align:middle line:84%
of who they were by
being with the men,

00:26:06.000 --> 00:26:10.783 align:middle line:84%
and they try and aspire to
be with men -- or women,

00:26:10.783 --> 00:26:15.535 align:middle line:84%
but they really try to be
recognized and seen and belong

00:26:15.535 --> 00:26:16.632 align:middle line:90%
to the group of men.

00:26:16.632 --> 00:26:19.050 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: And they took
responsibility at an earlier

00:26:19.050 --> 00:26:19.850 align:middle line:90%
age.

00:26:19.850 --> 00:26:20.669 align:middle line:90%
>> AV: Absolutely.

00:26:20.669 --> 00:26:23.972 align:middle line:84%
And then what happens
now is the holding tank

00:26:23.972 --> 00:26:28.215 align:middle line:84%
is the desire to be seen, to
show really the true colors

00:26:28.215 --> 00:26:33.415 align:middle line:84%
and to see them in themselves,
to be revealed to them.

00:26:33.415 --> 00:26:36.485 align:middle line:84%
But it doesn't happen because
they're sitting in school.

00:26:36.485 --> 00:26:39.058 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: It's interesting, because
there is a school in Russia

00:26:39.058 --> 00:26:42.393 align:middle line:84%
right now that is -- it's
associated with the concepts

00:26:42.393 --> 00:26:45.261 align:middle line:84%
put forth in the Anastasia
Ringing Cedars series,

00:26:45.261 --> 00:26:49.265 align:middle line:84%
and I asked you off camera if
you were familiar with this --

00:26:49.265 --> 00:26:53.936 align:middle line:84%
yeah, and in this particular
school people are learning it

00:26:53.936 --> 00:26:55.271 align:middle line:90%
this way.

00:26:55.271 --> 00:26:57.740 align:middle line:84%
The children come because they
choose to, boys and girls.

00:26:57.740 --> 00:27:02.300 align:middle line:84%
And they are put into
very saturated curriculum

00:27:02.300 --> 00:27:04.980 align:middle line:84%
based on their own desire,
propensities, needs,

00:27:04.980 --> 00:27:07.850 align:middle line:84%
what they're curious about, and
they learn everything they can,

00:27:07.850 --> 00:27:09.518 align:middle line:90%
all different ages together.

00:27:09.518 --> 00:27:11.453 align:middle line:84%
And they mentor and
teach each other.

00:27:11.453 --> 00:27:13.164 align:middle line:84%
It might be the
12 year old that's

00:27:13.164 --> 00:27:14.789 align:middle line:84%
really getting the
advanced mathematics

00:27:14.789 --> 00:27:17.059 align:middle line:84%
and they turn out
to be the leader

00:27:17.059 --> 00:27:18.594 align:middle line:90%
of that particular group.

00:27:18.594 --> 00:27:21.263 align:middle line:84%
But they learn in
a saturated way,

00:27:21.263 --> 00:27:25.109 align:middle line:84%
things that are not only
educational but very useful

00:27:25.109 --> 00:27:27.036 align:middle line:90%
for their own lives.

00:27:27.036 --> 00:27:29.538 align:middle line:84%
They learn -- the boys
learn how to build things,

00:27:29.538 --> 00:27:32.441 align:middle line:84%
the girls can learn if they
want to build things as well,

00:27:32.441 --> 00:27:35.420 align:middle line:84%
and then they learn to make
the place beautiful by using

00:27:35.420 --> 00:27:37.313 align:middle line:84%
artistic painting,
in particular,

00:27:37.313 --> 00:27:41.183 align:middle line:84%
to make the home domain they're
creating very beautiful.

00:27:41.183 --> 00:27:42.985 align:middle line:84%
And this brings up
the whole notion

00:27:42.985 --> 00:27:45.301 align:middle line:84%
of the educational
system we have

00:27:45.301 --> 00:27:47.122 align:middle line:84%
now, which I know
you unplugged from,

00:27:47.122 --> 00:27:50.644 align:middle line:84%
you said I'm not learning, this
is not teaching me what I need

00:27:50.644 --> 00:27:54.196 align:middle line:84%
to learn, and having it
integrate with what we chose

00:27:54.196 --> 00:27:55.898 align:middle line:90%
to become in our lives.

00:27:55.898 --> 00:27:58.400 align:middle line:84%
This is a radical reformation
that's needed in her.

00:27:58.400 --> 00:27:59.668 align:middle line:90%
>> AV: Absolutely --

00:27:59.668 --> 00:28:01.904 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: And as you say,
mentorship, apprenticeship --

00:28:01.904 --> 00:28:03.529 align:middle line:84%
>> AV: -- the more
I work with -- also,

00:28:03.529 --> 00:28:06.775 align:middle line:84%
using the hands by the
way, using hands to create.

00:28:06.775 --> 00:28:07.602 align:middle line:90%
Very important.

00:28:07.602 --> 00:28:09.144 align:middle line:84%
Been doing this for
a thousand years,

00:28:09.144 --> 00:28:13.200 align:middle line:84%
and now all of a sudden we
need to -- computer literate.

00:28:13.200 --> 00:28:14.617 align:middle line:84%
I mean, nothing
wrong, but what --

00:28:14.617 --> 00:28:19.255 align:middle line:84%
think of the loss of the craft
of the sensuality of work

00:28:19.255 --> 00:28:22.764 align:middle line:84%
and the connection you create
with your environment as you

00:28:22.764 --> 00:28:25.960 align:middle line:84%
take a piece of wood and you
start carving it or modifying

00:28:25.960 --> 00:28:28.297 align:middle line:84%
it to create a
chair or something.

00:28:28.297 --> 00:28:34.770 align:middle line:84%
It's a -- it's something that
we're really wired, you know,

00:28:34.770 --> 00:28:38.474 align:middle line:90%
the ability in order, right?

00:28:38.474 --> 00:28:44.680 align:middle line:84%
So they say it's really the
way to integrate a spiritual

00:28:44.680 --> 00:28:47.950 align:middle line:84%
experience which is the
experience of prayer or --

00:28:47.950 --> 00:28:49.818 align:middle line:90%
is labor, is using the --

00:28:49.818 --> 00:28:50.787 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Labor -- yes.

00:28:50.787 --> 00:28:52.454 align:middle line:84%
>> AV: Using the
hands, using the hands.

00:28:52.454 --> 00:28:54.023 align:middle line:90%
We need to digest this.

00:28:54.023 --> 00:28:56.258 align:middle line:84%
I mean, this is all, like,
a thousand years or so

00:28:56.258 --> 00:28:59.295 align:middle line:84%
of spiritual evolution is
like, where has it gone,

00:28:59.295 --> 00:29:01.563 align:middle line:90%
it's not there anymore.

00:29:01.563 --> 00:29:05.100 align:middle line:84%
It's another loss because
we have, like, to go this,

00:29:05.100 --> 00:29:06.569 align:middle line:90%
and this, and you have to do --

00:29:06.569 --> 00:29:09.069 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: Let's talk about the
kind of boys that find their way

00:29:09.069 --> 00:29:09.869 align:middle line:90%
to you.

00:29:09.869 --> 00:29:11.785 align:middle line:84%
And is it usually
the parents who

00:29:11.785 --> 00:29:14.231 align:middle line:84%
are looking for you
to help their sons,

00:29:14.231 --> 00:29:17.969 align:middle line:84%
or are the sons somehow coming
to you through some other group

00:29:17.969 --> 00:29:22.584 align:middle line:84%
or mechanism, and are they often
disconnected and, you know,

00:29:22.584 --> 00:29:24.969 align:middle line:84%
basically playing video
games and doing the standards

00:29:24.969 --> 00:29:25.888 align:middle line:90%
things kids do now?

00:29:25.888 --> 00:29:30.960 align:middle line:84%
>> AV: Video games -- that's
how it started, this problem,

00:29:30.960 --> 00:29:31.760 align:middle line:90%
actually.

00:29:31.760 --> 00:29:37.933 align:middle line:84%
I did this massive
initiation, basically in 1997,

00:29:37.933 --> 00:29:41.970 align:middle line:84%
and it was this -- it
was a program after that,

00:29:41.970 --> 00:29:47.109 align:middle line:84%
I thought it was very
valuable and I learned a lot,

00:29:47.109 --> 00:29:50.846 align:middle line:84%
it allowed me to be with other
men, and it was beautiful work.

00:29:50.846 --> 00:29:56.952 align:middle line:84%
And then because maybe
somebody got turned on to me,

00:29:56.952 --> 00:29:59.057 align:middle line:84%
I remember my father or
something -- obviously,

00:29:59.057 --> 00:30:02.991 align:middle line:84%
the sons of my friend were
sitting Saturdays home,

00:30:02.991 --> 00:30:07.396 align:middle line:84%
playing computers, because they
don't go anywhere, you know,

00:30:07.396 --> 00:30:10.232 align:middle line:84%
the [INAUDIBLE] and I said well,
next Saturday come with me,

00:30:10.232 --> 00:30:11.700 align:middle line:90%
I'll take you surfing.

00:30:11.700 --> 00:30:14.536 align:middle line:90%
And that's how we started.

00:30:14.536 --> 00:30:18.173 align:middle line:84%
Take the kids surfing,
which is challenging.

00:30:18.173 --> 00:30:20.175 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: Were they resistant
to it or were they --

00:30:20.175 --> 00:30:24.123 align:middle line:84%
>> AV: Well, I wasn't their
father, so it was cool,

00:30:24.123 --> 00:30:25.514 align:middle line:90%
you know?

00:30:25.514 --> 00:30:31.036 align:middle line:84%
Surfing was the excuse for
them to show up on time,

00:30:31.036 --> 00:30:32.554 align:middle line:90%
ready to go.

00:30:32.554 --> 00:30:34.323 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: And they
willingly did this?

00:30:34.323 --> 00:30:35.723 align:middle line:90%
>> AV: Not willingly.

00:30:35.723 --> 00:30:37.994 align:middle line:84%
To do it willingly,
there are consequences.

00:30:37.994 --> 00:30:38.794 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Right.

00:30:38.794 --> 00:30:39.795 align:middle line:90%
Okay.

00:30:39.795 --> 00:30:41.563 align:middle line:84%
>> AV: They had to
pay consequences.

00:30:41.563 --> 00:30:47.602 align:middle line:84%
And so they get it, there's no
negotiation, it's 8 o'clock,

00:30:47.602 --> 00:30:49.071 align:middle line:90%
it's 8 o'clock.

00:30:49.071 --> 00:30:51.106 align:middle line:84%
And if you're not there,
there are consequences.

00:30:51.106 --> 00:30:56.011 align:middle line:84%
It's not punishment,
consequences, right?

00:30:56.011 --> 00:31:00.315 align:middle line:84%
So they'd be there 8
o'clock and they're ready,

00:31:00.315 --> 00:31:03.886 align:middle line:84%
so we can go have fun,
instead of take care of the --

00:31:03.886 --> 00:31:05.020 align:middle line:90%
>> RM:

00:31:05.020 --> 00:31:07.423 align:middle line:84%
>> AV: And was there a
transformative moment for these

00:31:07.423 --> 00:31:08.223 align:middle line:90%
boys?

00:31:08.223 --> 00:31:11.726 align:middle line:84%
Did they end up saying hey, yes,
after the first time or so, did

00:31:11.726 --> 00:31:13.929 align:middle line:84%
they want to get up
and go or did they --

00:31:13.929 --> 00:31:16.425 align:middle line:84%
was it something you had
