outside of the family

00:32:20.472 --> 00:32:22.492 align:middle line:84%
structure, outside of
the educational structure

00:32:22.492 --> 00:32:24.800 align:middle line:84%
and so forth, where they're
just there, as you say,

00:32:24.800 --> 00:32:27.736 align:middle line:84%
to work it out in these
weekends together.

00:32:27.736 --> 00:32:31.641 align:middle line:84%
Do you notice that they do --
already have an idea of what

00:32:31.641 --> 00:32:32.441 align:middle line:90%
their purpose is?

00:32:32.441 --> 00:32:33.476 align:middle line:90%
>> AV: Absolutely.

00:32:33.476 --> 00:32:34.476 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Most of the time?

00:32:34.476 --> 00:32:35.677 align:middle line:90%
>> AV: Absolutely.

00:32:35.677 --> 00:32:38.766 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: Because you talk to most
adult men right now and they

00:32:38.766 --> 00:32:42.184 align:middle line:84%
have no idea what they're
here for or want to do.

00:32:42.184 --> 00:32:44.086 align:middle line:90%
It's like it gets squashed out.

00:32:44.086 --> 00:32:45.815 align:middle line:84%
But you're saying
if you preempt it,

00:32:45.815 --> 00:32:49.760 align:middle line:84%
if you catch it early and foster
it, they know this already?

00:32:49.760 --> 00:32:51.260 align:middle line:84%
>> AV: Yeah, this
is very important,

00:32:51.260 --> 00:32:54.596 align:middle line:84%
because I'm not a teacher,
I don't invent the wheel,

00:32:54.596 --> 00:32:56.598 align:middle line:90%
the wheel is already there.

00:32:56.598 --> 00:33:00.333 align:middle line:84%
My job is to find
a grammar so it can

00:33:00.333 --> 00:33:02.504 align:middle line:90%
be drawn out and recognized.

00:33:02.504 --> 00:33:04.406 align:middle line:90%
That is a skill.

00:33:04.406 --> 00:33:06.836 align:middle line:84%
And it's not something
you can learn in schools,

00:33:06.836 --> 00:33:08.511 align:middle line:84%
you know, you have
to be a little weird,

00:33:08.511 --> 00:33:09.511 align:middle line:90%
that's my qualification.

00:33:09.511 --> 00:33:10.928 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: Yeah, a
little weird, yeah.

00:33:10.928 --> 00:33:14.650 align:middle line:84%
>> AV: A little weird, weird
enough so you understand --

00:33:14.650 --> 00:33:18.320 align:middle line:84%
because they resonate with
your weirdness, really.

00:33:18.320 --> 00:33:21.250 align:middle line:84%
And because they're at a weird
time in their life, that's

00:33:21.250 --> 00:33:23.559 align:middle line:84%
the time they're
officially weird,

00:33:23.559 --> 00:33:25.260 align:middle line:90%
and I'm officially weird myself.

00:33:25.260 --> 00:33:28.330 align:middle line:84%
So there's a way we
can mirror each other.

00:33:28.330 --> 00:33:30.311 align:middle line:84%
I mentioned to
you the other time

00:33:30.311 --> 00:33:32.693 align:middle line:84%
we spoke when I
was a kid, when I

00:33:32.693 --> 00:33:35.704 align:middle line:84%
was a young boy, what happened
when I was in first grade.

00:33:35.704 --> 00:33:39.942 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: Yes, tell us about that
again, that was off camera.

00:33:39.942 --> 00:33:42.494 align:middle line:84%
>> AV: There was the teacher
took a liking to me in first

00:33:42.494 --> 00:33:47.066 align:middle line:84%
grade, and the other teacher --
the other mothers got jealous

00:33:47.066 --> 00:33:50.050 align:middle line:84%
and made it -- protested
with the head master,

00:33:50.050 --> 00:33:52.315 align:middle line:84%
and the head master
walked in the class,

00:33:52.315 --> 00:33:57.169 align:middle line:84%
sat down in front of me, and
went to find out if I'm really

00:33:57.169 --> 00:33:59.795 align:middle line:84%
that smart genius my
teacher thought I was.

00:33:59.795 --> 00:34:06.169 align:middle line:84%
This was the last time any woman
thought I was a smart genius --

00:34:06.169 --> 00:34:06.969 align:middle line:90%
[laughter] but --

00:34:06.969 --> 00:34:08.302 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Jealous mothers, okay.

00:34:08.302 --> 00:34:14.290 align:middle line:84%
>> AV: So the teacher
ran me through some test,

00:34:14.290 --> 00:34:16.578 align:middle line:90%
and I aced them.

00:34:16.578 --> 00:34:21.026 align:middle line:84%
I don't remember if
[INAUDIBLE] and the head master

00:34:21.026 --> 00:34:27.723 align:middle line:84%
was very pleased with himself,
he had this grin on his face.

00:34:27.723 --> 00:34:34.563 align:middle line:84%
And when I seen that, I was
filled with a cold fury.

00:34:34.563 --> 00:34:36.098 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Why?

00:34:36.098 --> 00:34:39.101 align:middle line:84%
>> AV: Well, it took me
fifty years to find out.

00:34:39.101 --> 00:34:41.637 align:middle line:84%
But it was a cold
fury, and it said --

00:34:41.637 --> 00:34:46.408 align:middle line:84%
the voice spoke inside me, and
said how dare you think that

00:34:46.408 --> 00:34:53.014 align:middle line:84%
this, knowing 1 plus
1 equals 2 defines me.

00:34:53.014 --> 00:34:55.050 align:middle line:84%
But I wasn't the
one thinking this,

00:34:55.050 --> 00:34:57.586 align:middle line:84%
it was a bigger thing
thinking this thing.

00:34:57.586 --> 00:35:00.373 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: Yeah, the
larger part of yourself

00:35:00.373 --> 00:35:01.790 align:middle line:84%
>> AV: Really, the
physical sense,

00:35:01.790 --> 00:35:06.328 align:middle line:84%
I remember now being
expanded inside.

00:35:06.328 --> 00:35:10.432 align:middle line:84%
So all our -- they call it
an education system is based

00:35:10.432 --> 00:35:11.400 align:middle line:90%
on this, right?

00:35:11.400 --> 00:35:17.406 align:middle line:84%
What happened to this rest
of the beautiful thing that

00:35:17.406 --> 00:35:18.206 align:middle line:90%
happens?

00:35:18.206 --> 00:35:23.627 align:middle line:84%
You know, as my friend
and coach says, 1 plus 1

00:35:23.627 --> 00:35:25.514 align:middle line:90%
is equals amazing.

00:35:25.514 --> 00:35:27.382 align:middle line:90%
And 1 plus 1 equals 2.

00:35:27.382 --> 00:35:29.902 align:middle line:84%
They're both -- you have to
be able to have them both

00:35:29.902 --> 00:35:30.702 align:middle line:90%
together.

00:35:30.702 --> 00:35:33.689 align:middle line:84%
So I had this vision, and
literally took me fifty years

00:35:33.689 --> 00:35:36.623 align:middle line:84%
to find out, because
we're in a world where

00:35:36.623 --> 00:35:38.260 align:middle line:90%
privilege is 1 plus 1.

00:35:38.260 --> 00:35:41.752 align:middle line:84%
If your privilege
is another thing,

00:35:41.752 --> 00:35:44.666 align:middle line:90%
you're going to be weird.

00:35:44.666 --> 00:35:48.680 align:middle line:84%
So it takes a long time to
really become comfortable with

00:35:48.680 --> 00:35:52.724 align:middle line:84%
this -- this is the first vision
six years old is a tough vision

00:35:52.724 --> 00:35:53.842 align:middle line:90%
to carry.

00:35:53.842 --> 00:35:55.883 align:middle line:84%
Also, you're not going
to talk to your mom,

00:35:55.883 --> 00:35:57.925 align:middle line:84%
because your mom is going
to say come on, go play

00:35:57.925 --> 00:35:58.747 align:middle line:90%
with your sister.

00:35:58.747 --> 00:36:01.501 align:middle line:84%
And rightly so,
because your mama

00:36:01.501 --> 00:36:06.288 align:middle line:84%
has to deal with the heroic
purpose of putting food

00:36:06.288 --> 00:36:07.556 align:middle line:90%
on the table, you know?

00:36:07.556 --> 00:36:08.890 align:middle line:90%
And it's other functions.

00:36:08.890 --> 00:36:11.946 align:middle line:84%
Where do you go
with this, I'm not

00:36:11.946 --> 00:36:15.864 align:middle line:84%
the only one with these
kinds of visions, right?

00:36:15.864 --> 00:36:17.568 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: But still
at six years old,

00:36:17.568 --> 00:36:20.523 align:middle line:84%
it was kind of defining where
your boundaries were at a very

00:36:20.523 --> 00:36:22.170 align:middle line:84%
early age and what
you were going to --

00:36:22.170 --> 00:36:24.940 align:middle line:84%
>> AV: Correct, when
I'm 18, I'm in college,

00:36:24.940 --> 00:36:27.976 align:middle line:84%
I look at the professor teaching
and he's a very smart guy,

00:36:27.976 --> 00:36:30.579 align:middle line:84%
very intelligent, very
articulate, brilliant.

00:36:30.579 --> 00:36:32.314 align:middle line:84%
But there's a voice
that comes inside me

00:36:32.314 --> 00:36:34.382 align:middle line:84%
and says the guy
doesn't know anywhere,

00:36:34.382 --> 00:36:36.312 align:middle line:90%
you've got to go somewhere else.

00:36:36.312 --> 00:36:38.687 align:middle line:84%
So you drop out of college,
I went to India and so forth.

00:36:38.687 --> 00:36:39.688 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: You went to
India for years,

00:36:39.688 --> 00:36:41.089 align:middle line:84%
you went on the
great journey, yeah.

00:36:41.089 --> 00:36:41.890 align:middle line:90%
>> AV: Right.

00:36:41.890 --> 00:36:43.024 align:middle line:90%
I went to the great journey.

00:36:43.024 --> 00:36:44.760 align:middle line:84%
But it takes -- and this
is really what I bring

00:36:44.760 --> 00:36:45.694 align:middle line:90%
to the plate.

00:36:45.694 --> 00:36:48.048 align:middle line:84%
I said let's look
for that thing.

00:36:48.048 --> 00:36:49.631 align:middle line:84%
I don't know how
it's going to happen,

00:36:49.631 --> 00:36:51.199 align:middle line:84%
I don't know how it's
going to come forth.

00:36:51.199 --> 00:36:53.532 align:middle line:84%
It might be doing a sweat
lodge -- might be while you --

00:36:53.532 --> 00:36:58.306 align:middle line:84%
might be while you climb
-- do something crazy,

00:36:58.306 --> 00:37:00.642 align:middle line:84%
maybe you create a poem,
maybe it will be --

00:37:00.642 --> 00:37:02.444 align:middle line:84%
I don't know where
it's going to happen.

00:37:02.444 --> 00:37:05.059 align:middle line:84%
But I'm going to create
opportunities for this

00:37:05.059 --> 00:37:06.581 align:middle line:90%
to come up.

00:37:06.581 --> 00:37:09.484 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: So when you do this,
obviously this is what you do,

00:37:09.484 --> 00:37:11.553 align:middle line:84%
you facilitate these
moments of awakening.

00:37:11.553 --> 00:37:12.954 align:middle line:90%
>> AV: Correct.

00:37:12.954 --> 00:37:15.966 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: And so you're seeing
by the age of 12, 13,

00:37:15.966 --> 00:37:20.246 align:middle line:84%
14 years old, they know,
they really know inside what

00:37:20.246 --> 00:37:23.100 align:middle line:84%
their purpose is or what they
want, what they want to do.

00:37:23.100 --> 00:37:25.267 align:middle line:84%
>> AV: They know there's
something bigger than that.

00:37:25.267 --> 00:37:27.869 align:middle line:84%
They don't know, they're
going against the current,

00:37:27.869 --> 00:37:31.239 align:middle line:84%
the current says it wants to
put you in these little boxes.

00:37:31.239 --> 00:37:33.635 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: I understand,
there's a mental disconnect.

00:37:33.635 --> 00:37:35.677 align:middle line:84%
>> AV: And they don't know
that this is possible,

00:37:35.677 --> 00:37:39.753 align:middle line:84%
there's a territory of vision
that is impossible and is

00:37:39.753 --> 00:37:41.416 align:middle line:90%
actually around you.

00:37:41.416 --> 00:37:44.920 align:middle line:90%
You swim in it all the time.

00:37:44.920 --> 00:37:48.223 align:middle line:84%
And that's why I use nature,
because nature is fantastic,

00:37:48.223 --> 00:37:52.761 align:middle line:84%
you can sit in front with
ceremonies in front of trees

00:37:52.761 --> 00:37:54.796 align:middle line:90%
and have incredibly revealing.

00:37:54.796 --> 00:37:55.969 align:middle line:90%
Because they get it.

00:37:55.969 --> 00:37:57.677 align:middle line:84%
I don't tell them
what's going to happen,

00:37:57.677 --> 00:37:59.914 align:middle line:84%
I don't, but they
get the message,

00:37:59.914 --> 00:38:01.369 align:middle line:90%
whatever needs to happen.

00:38:01.369 --> 00:38:03.786 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: When you're working
with boys you don't talk a lot,

00:38:03.786 --> 00:38:06.641 align:middle line:84%
there's not a lot of
information shared verbally,

00:38:06.641 --> 00:38:09.911 align:middle line:84%
it's all experiential, which is
as you say at that age you have

00:38:09.911 --> 00:38:13.842 align:middle line:84%
to reach out and
touch whatever it is.

00:38:13.842 --> 00:38:15.550 align:middle line:84%
>> AV: As Brad said,
they learn by doing,

00:38:15.550 --> 00:38:17.811 align:middle line:84%
they learn by being
treated by men,

00:38:17.811 --> 00:38:20.857 align:middle line:84%
we treat them like they're ten
years old and then they are.

00:38:20.857 --> 00:38:22.524 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: So they have
full responsibility?

00:38:22.524 --> 00:38:23.859 align:middle line:90%
>> AV: Full responsibility.

00:38:23.859 --> 00:38:27.429 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: How does that -- what
does that weekend look like

00:38:27.429 --> 00:38:28.763 align:middle line:90%
or that time together?

00:38:28.763 --> 00:38:32.067 align:middle line:84%
>> AV: Well, I've got to tell
you a little bit about it,

00:38:32.067 --> 00:38:34.410 align:middle line:84%
because it changes, depends
on the communities where you

00:38:34.410 --> 00:38:35.210 align:middle line:90%
produce it.

00:38:35.210 --> 00:38:36.460 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: That makes sense, sure.

00:38:36.460 --> 00:38:38.752 align:middle line:84%
>> AV: If I go to Canada,
it's going to be one weekend.

00:38:38.752 --> 00:38:41.076 align:middle line:84%
If I go to California it's
going to be another weekend.

00:38:41.076 --> 00:38:42.511 align:middle line:84%
If I do it here it's going
to be another weekend.

00:38:42.511 --> 00:38:44.512 align:middle line:84%
It depends on the
man with the brain,

00:38:44.512 --> 00:38:46.748 align:middle line:84%
because it's also
important to understand --

00:38:46.748 --> 00:38:47.916 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: Because they have
an imprint of their culture

00:38:47.916 --> 00:38:48.716 align:middle line:90%
on them, of course.

00:38:48.716 --> 00:38:49.754 align:middle line:90%
>> AV: Absolutely.

00:38:49.754 --> 00:38:51.129 align:middle line:84%
And then for us,
the men that are

00:38:51.129 --> 00:38:53.503 align:middle line:84%
going to work with me, it's
not about looking good,

00:38:53.503 --> 00:38:57.526 align:middle line:84%
it's not about the degrees,
it's not about the grief.

00:38:57.526 --> 00:38:58.326 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Grief?

00:38:58.326 --> 00:38:59.794 align:middle line:90%
>> AV: Correct.

00:38:59.794 --> 00:39:03.131 align:middle line:84%
Because a person's initiation
is a person going down.

00:39:03.131 --> 00:39:06.234 align:middle line:84%
The beginning of the process
the person is going down.

00:39:06.234 --> 00:39:11.239 align:middle line:84%
And really, a way, the best
way for a man to hold his truth

00:39:11.239 --> 00:39:13.575 align:middle line:84%
and be honest is coming
up with his grief.

00:39:13.575 --> 00:39:16.164 align:middle line:84%
It's not about being
happy and successful.

00:39:16.164 --> 00:39:18.747 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: It's connecting with that
thing that breaks your heart.

00:39:18.747 --> 00:39:20.330 align:middle line:84%
>> AV: Correct,
that's what you bring,

00:39:20.330 --> 00:39:22.984 align:middle line:84%
that's going to make
you authentic and real.

00:39:22.984 --> 00:39:26.688 align:middle line:84%
Because boys, they
don't take bull.

00:39:26.688 --> 00:39:30.625 align:middle line:90%
They can smell you a mile away.

00:39:30.625 --> 00:39:33.962 align:middle line:84%
So I don't want people looking
good, I want people to be real.

00:39:33.962 --> 00:39:37.565 align:middle line:84%
If you're real, the
weekend is done, you know?

00:39:37.565 --> 00:39:38.767 align:middle line:90%
That is simple.

00:39:38.767 --> 00:39:41.937 align:middle line:84%
The people that work with
me and I work with them,

00:39:41.937 --> 00:39:46.542 align:middle line:84%
is that they require
me, absolutely, total --

00:39:46.542 --> 00:39:47.375 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Authenticity.

00:39:47.375 --> 00:39:49.044 align:middle line:90%
>> AV: Authenticity.

00:39:49.044 --> 00:39:54.683 align:middle line:84%
Generally speaking, it's
a process of separation.

00:39:54.683 --> 00:39:56.518 align:middle line:84%
The rite of passage
is separation.

00:39:56.518 --> 00:39:59.387 align:middle line:84%
They come from this world,
they go into another world.

00:39:59.387 --> 00:40:02.824 align:middle line:84%
We're not, we're
down the rabbit hole.

00:40:02.824 --> 00:40:04.392 align:middle line:84%
It's a person going
down to his hurt.

00:40:04.392 --> 00:40:07.529 align:middle line:84%
So they come for intellectual
perception of reality,

00:40:07.529 --> 00:40:11.166 align:middle line:84%
we go into intelligence
perception of reality.

00:40:11.166 --> 00:40:14.903 align:middle line:84%
And we achieve that by
an experiential thing.

00:40:14.903 --> 00:40:16.271 align:middle line:90%
So I make an example.

00:40:16.271 --> 00:40:18.840 align:middle line:84%
Come off the bus, been
two hours in this bus,

00:40:18.840 --> 00:40:21.656 align:middle line:84%
and they're all rowdy and
full of spunk and things.

00:40:21.656 --> 00:40:23.281 align:middle line:84%
They're coming down
this trail, there's

00:40:23.281 --> 00:40:25.947 align:middle line:84%
a trail that goes down to
the lake, it's two miles.

00:40:25.947 --> 00:40:30.785 align:middle line:84%
It's two miles in the woods
and there's nobody there.

00:40:30.785 --> 00:40:33.021 align:middle line:84%
They're instructed to
go down in the woods.

00:40:33.021 --> 00:40:37.826 align:middle line:84%
So the first thing
they hear is a man

00:40:37.826 --> 00:40:41.396 align:middle line:90%
who is doing this grief song.

00:40:41.396 --> 00:40:43.932 align:middle line:84%
And no one ever heard a
grief song, but something

00:40:43.932 --> 00:40:46.434 align:middle line:90%
that curdle your blood.

00:40:46.434 --> 00:40:49.124 align:middle line:84%
And they don't know what
it is, but you know,

00:40:49.124 --> 00:40:51.686 align:middle line:84%
so they're going down
this magic forest,

00:40:51.686 --> 00:40:56.411 align:middle line:84%
but now it becomes blessed
because of the singing.

00:40:56.411 --> 00:40:58.165 align:middle line:84%
So they come down
and it's -- oh,

00:40:58.165 --> 00:41:00.081 align:middle line:90%
we're not in Kansas any more.

00:41:00.081 --> 00:41:03.084 align:middle line:90%
They have to proceed, right?

00:41:03.084 --> 00:41:06.054 align:middle line:84%
So -- and then other
things happen on this walk,

00:41:06.054 --> 00:41:10.792 align:middle line:84%
they encounter homeless people,
they're laying in the middle

00:41:10.792 --> 00:41:14.096 align:middle line:84%
of the stream and tell them
don't go there, don't go back,

00:41:14.096 --> 00:41:14.896 align:middle line:90%
they're crazy.

00:41:14.896 --> 00:41:18.099 align:middle line:84%
And another guy in a suit
and passes by, this is like,

00:41:18.099 --> 00:41:20.935 align:middle line:84%
focus on things, go back
to things that are crazy.

00:41:20.935 --> 00:41:22.270 align:middle line:90%
So this is really strange.

00:41:22.270 --> 00:41:23.772 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: So it's
very disorienting?

00:41:23.772 --> 00:41:25.907 align:middle line:84%
>> AV: Disorient -- that's
exactly what we want.

00:41:25.907 --> 00:41:28.209 align:middle line:90%
And then there's a gate.

00:41:28.209 --> 00:41:30.945 align:middle line:84%
So there are three men standing
in the middle of the road,

00:41:30.945 --> 00:41:33.515 align:middle line:84%
and these three men
are dressed in ashes.

00:41:33.515 --> 00:41:35.583 align:middle line:90%
And they're painted.

00:41:35.583 --> 00:41:41.356 align:middle line:84%
And so they come, they
come, so -- usually it's me.

00:41:41.356 --> 00:41:44.993 align:middle line:84%
So they line up in front,
they have to go past us.

00:41:44.993 --> 00:41:51.232 align:middle line:84%
So there's -- and ask them,
